<Link id="l00172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="172"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The source register of a COPY machine instruction can be propagated to all</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="173"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// its users, and this propagation could increase the probability of finding</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="174"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// common subexpressions. If the COPY has only one user, the COPY itself can</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="175"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// be removed.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="176"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-machinecse-cpp-/machinecseimpl/#afa45f044e3446f2b12508c03b108e2d8">MachineCSEImpl</a>::PerformTrivialCopyPropagation(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/lib/codegen/globalisel/irtranslator-cpp/#abe44dfdea65b4f7e11e0a608ab708b76">MI</a>,</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="178"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/groups/arcopt/#gaa57b1a4e6a1c79233913139635169cf1">Changed</a> = </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">false</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00179" /><CodeLine lineNumber="179"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineoperand">MachineOperand</a> &amp;MO : <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/lib/codegen/globalisel/irtranslator-cpp/#abe44dfdea65b4f7e11e0a608ab708b76">MI</a>-&gt;all&#95;uses()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00180" /><CodeLine lineNumber="180"><span class="doxyHighlight">    Register Reg = MO.getReg();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00181" /><CodeLine lineNumber="181"><span class="doxyHighlight">    if (!Reg.isVirtual())</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="182"><span class="doxyHighlight">      continue;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00183" /><CodeLine lineNumber="183"><span class="doxyHighlight">    bool OnlyOneUse = MRI-&gt;hasOneNonDBGUse(Reg);</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00187" /><CodeLine lineNumber="187"><span class="doxyHighlight">    Register SrcReg = DefMI-&gt;getOperand(1).getReg();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00188" /><CodeLine lineNumber="188"><span class="doxyHighlight">    if (!SrcReg.isVirtual())</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00189" /><CodeLine lineNumber="189"><span class="doxyHighlight">      continue;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00190" /><CodeLine lineNumber="190"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// FIXME: We should trivially coalesce subregister copies to expose CSE</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00191" /><CodeLine lineNumber="191"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// opportunities on instructions with truncated operands (see</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00192" /><CodeLine lineNumber="192"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// cse-add-with-overflow.ll). This can be done here as follows:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00193" /><CodeLine lineNumber="193"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// if (SrcSubReg)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00194" /><CodeLine lineNumber="194"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  RC = TRI-&gt;getMatchingSuperRegClass(MRI-&gt;getRegClass(SrcReg), RC,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00195" /><CodeLine lineNumber="195"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                                     SrcSubReg);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00196" /><CodeLine lineNumber="196"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// MO.substVirtReg(SrcReg, SrcSubReg, &#42;TRI);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00197" /><CodeLine lineNumber="197"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00198" /><CodeLine lineNumber="198"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The 2-addr pass has been updated to handle coalesced subregs. However,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00199" /><CodeLine lineNumber="199"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// some machine-specific code still can&#39;t handle it.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00200" /><CodeLine lineNumber="200"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// To handle it properly we also need a way find a constrained subregister</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00201" /><CodeLine lineNumber="201"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// class given a super-reg class and subreg index.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00208" /><CodeLine lineNumber="208"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00209" /><CodeLine lineNumber="209"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Propagate SrcReg of copies to MI.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00212" /><CodeLine lineNumber="212"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Coalesce single use copies.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00213" /><CodeLine lineNumber="213"><span class="doxyHighlight">    if (OnlyOneUse) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00218" /><CodeLine lineNumber="218"></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00221" /><CodeLine lineNumber="221"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00227" /><CodeLine lineNumber="227"></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00608" /><CodeLine lineNumber="608"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Prevent CSE-ing non-local convergent instructions.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00609" /><CodeLine lineNumber="609"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// LLVM&#39;s current definition of &#96;isConvergent&#96; does not necessarily prove</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00610" /><CodeLine lineNumber="610"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// that non-local CSE is illegal. The following check extends the definition</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00611" /><CodeLine lineNumber="611"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// of &#96;isConvergent&#96; to assume a convergent instruction is dependent not</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00612" /><CodeLine lineNumber="612"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// only on additional conditions, but also on fewer conditions. LLVM does</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00613" /><CodeLine lineNumber="613"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// not have a MachineInstr attribute which expresses this extended</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00614" /><CodeLine lineNumber="614"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// definition, so it&#39;s necessary to use &#96;isConvergent&#96; to prevent illegally</span></CodeLine>
